# Code Quality Rules

## Making Changes
- Verify information before presenting it — do not assume or speculate
- Make changes file by file
- Provide all edits in a single chunk per file, not multi-step instructions
- Don't remove unrelated code or functionalities — preserve existing structures
- Don't suggest updates when there are no actual modifications needed
- Don't invent changes other than what's explicitly requested

## Code Standards
- Use explicit variable names over short ambiguous ones
- Follow the existing coding style in the project for consistency
- Prioritize code performance where applicable
- Security-first approach — always consider security implications
- Implement robust error handling and logging
- Encourage modular design for maintainability and reusability
- Consider and handle edge cases
- Ensure changes are compatible with Python 3.12+

## Do NOT
- Add comments that just narrate what code does
- Use apologies or understanding feedback in comments
- Suggest whitespace-only changes
- Summarize changes — just make them
- Ask for confirmation of information already in context
